messages.content: The `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin is a simple GUI element that allows for creating a grid of images.
How can I preview the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin?

You can preview the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin by visiting the URL <https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin/blob/main/.readme/preview.png>. The XYZPlot feature is similar to auto1111 but with more settings, and the integration with [`efficiency`](https://github.com/LucianoCirino/efficiency-nodes-comfyui) can also be previewed.
How do I use the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin?

To use the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin, you need to first download the latest stable release from <https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin/archive/refs/heads/main.zip> and then unpack the node into the `custom_nodes` folder.
Where can I find more information about the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin?
You can find more information about the `ImagesGrid` Comfy Plugin at its source, which is <https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin>.
